Sure thing, Mary! I'd be happy to share some of my favorite electronic music tracks and artists with you. I've recently been hooked on a math-rock band called "Equationic." Their sound captures the abstract beauty of mathematical concepts through soothing harmonies, much like how Algebrahythmic intertwines mathematical concepts and upbeat electronic music. You might also enjoy "Luigi Tesaverso," who creates music that explores the relationship between math and sound, as well as "Ethereal Algorithm," whose music is heavily inspired by mathematical and computational concepts. I think incorporating these artists into our bouldering event will create a unique and immersive experience, one that highlights the connections between music, math, and physical activity.

In addition to these music recommendations, I'm also interested in exploring interactive art installations that showcase the math and art connection. I recently discovered "The Sonic Pattern," which uses bouldering holds to create unique soundscapes based on the patterns and positions of the holds. Climbers unknowingly compose music as they scale the walls, creating a perfect blend of our shared interests. This installation, along with the "rhythm remix" challenge and the "synth pad station," will inspire climbers to discover their unique talents and interests in bouldering and beyond. #

